WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:02.915
<i>Previously on "Will Trent"...</i>

00:02.915 --> 00:04.439
- It's not her. That's Kayla!
- Are you sure?

00:04.439 --> 00:07.050
- Abigail! It's not Emma!
- What?

00:07.050 --> 00:09.226
Put out an Amber Alert.
This is a kidnapping.

00:09.226 --> 00:11.359
Agent Trent, this is
Detective Faith Mitchell.

00:11.359 --> 00:12.969
No partners.
That was our agreement.

00:12.969 --> 00:14.188
You've never worked
an active kidnapping.

00:14.188 --> 00:16.364
Let's be clear--
neither of us is thrilled

00:16.364 --> 00:18.018
about this arrangement,
so let's just be polite

00:18.018 --> 00:19.149
and get through this case.

00:19.149 --> 00:21.760
Should Detective Polaski
stay in vice,

00:21.760 --> 00:23.066
with all her vices?

00:23.066 --> 00:24.502
Well, maybe a change of scene
would be good.

00:24.502 --> 00:25.982
I need someone
to keep an eye on you.

00:25.982 --> 00:27.462
No one's tougher than Ormewood.

00:27.462 --> 00:29.986
Ahh! I didn't mean
to kill anybody, man!

00:29.986 --> 00:31.988
<i>Listen to me.
Let's just bring Emma home.</i>

00:31.988 --> 00:34.599
I don't know where she is!

00:34.599 --> 00:35.557
Then tell me
who your partner is.

00:35.557 --> 00:36.993
I can't!

00:36.993 --> 00:38.777
I really messed up.
I need your help.

00:38.777 --> 00:39.996
- What happened?
- I shot him.

00:39.996 --> 00:41.911
- Who?
- The man that took Emma.

00:45.697 --> 00:47.569
Mr. Campano,
it's the middle of the night.

00:47.569 --> 00:49.049
You've been drinking.
I need you to leave.

00:49.049 --> 00:51.007
Where is she? Huh?

00:51.007 --> 00:52.139
I don't know what
you're talking about!

00:52.139 --> 00:53.749
Where is she?!
Don't tell me-- Don't--

00:53.749 --> 00:55.098
If you don't leave,
I'm gonna call the police.

00:55.098 --> 00:56.839
No, I know about you.
I know about you!

00:56.839 --> 00:58.145
- Where is my daughter?
- You are out of your mind!

00:58.145 --> 01:00.277
- I'm going in my house!
- Hey, hey, hey!

01:00.277 --> 01:01.670
Don't you--

01:01.670 --> 01:04.020
Don't you walk away from me!

01:04.020 --> 01:06.109
Aah!

01:06.109 --> 01:07.893
What?

01:16.946 --> 01:18.165
What the hell did you do, huh?

01:18.165 --> 01:19.514
It was an accident.

01:19.514 --> 01:21.472
You need to tell me what
happened. Betty, shut up.

01:21.472 --> 01:23.387
God, you smell like you
climbed out of a bottle of gin.

01:23.387 --> 01:25.389
Yeah, you jealous?
You used to hit it pretty
hard back in the day.

01:25.389 --> 01:26.608
All right. Take it easy, Paul.

01:26.608 --> 01:27.870
I do have a badge and a gun
these days.

01:27.870 --> 01:29.089
Both of you shut up.

01:29.089 --> 01:30.873
Betty, I'm not gonna
say it again. I mean it.

01:31.961 --> 01:33.397
Hey, what happened?

01:33.397 --> 01:35.051
- Where are my pants?
- Living room.

01:35.051 --> 01:36.879
- I was--
- Tell me.

01:36.879 --> 01:37.967
Evan Bernard.

01:37.967 --> 01:40.056
Emma's English teacher.

01:40.056 --> 01:42.928
Emma and this... pervert

01:42.928 --> 01:44.539
were working
on a project together.

01:44.539 --> 01:46.976
A lot of office hours
behind closed doors.

01:46.976 --> 01:48.543
And then, out of the blue,

01:48.543 --> 01:50.762
she just wanted to transfer
to another class.

01:50.762 --> 01:52.938
And you think something
happened between them.

01:52.938 --> 01:55.071
No. No. I don't think,
I know, okay? I know!

01:55.071 --> 01:56.768
I mean, she shut down.

01:56.768 --> 01:58.727
She stopped caring
about anything,

01:58.727 --> 02:01.469
and I was just too busy opening
up new locations to notice.

02:01.469 --> 02:04.167
But I-- I just went there
to-- to talk with him.

02:04.167 --> 02:05.299
I didn't-- I didn't mean
to hurt him, Trash.

02:05.299 --> 02:06.561
That's hard to sell

02:06.561 --> 02:08.084
considering you took the gun
over there.

02:08.084 --> 02:09.216
Don't call him Trash,
by the way.

02:09.216 --> 02:10.521
Just listen to me!

02:10.521 --> 02:12.784
You two of all people
should understand.

02:12.784 --> 02:14.569
Where we came from?

02:14.569 --> 02:16.658
I think we all know
how to spot a predator.

02:20.009 --> 02:21.358
Is that your blood or his?

02:21.358 --> 02:23.534
It's his.

02:23.534 --> 02:25.101
- You got a bag in there?
- Kitchen.

02:25.101 --> 02:27.495
Middle drawer next to the sink.

02:27.495 --> 02:28.583
Take off your shirt.

02:30.150 --> 02:32.152
- Ang, you got handcuffs?
- Always!

02:33.588 --> 02:34.937
Give me the shirt.

02:34.937 --> 02:36.373
We need his DNA.

02:37.157 --> 02:38.332
Now we're gonna
have to arrest you

02:38.332 --> 02:40.203
because you shot a man
in his driveway.

02:40.203 --> 02:42.553
And if you're right,
then everything else we do

02:42.553 --> 02:45.034
needs to be by the book--
if he's still alive.

02:45.034 --> 02:47.428
I can't believe you guys
are still hooking up.

02:47.428 --> 02:48.603
You know, there's
a whole world out there

02:48.603 --> 02:49.952
full of people, right?

02:49.952 --> 02:51.432
Thank you for the life advice.

02:51.432 --> 02:52.955
You have the right
to remain silent.

02:52.955 --> 02:54.130
Anything you say can and will be

02:54.130 --> 02:56.176
used against you
in a court of law.

03:04.140 --> 03:06.142
Ambulance is on the way.

03:06.142 --> 03:08.013
He's still breathing.

03:08.013 --> 03:10.146
His pulse is weak and thready.

03:10.146 --> 03:11.669
Two pools of blood. He moved.

03:11.669 --> 03:14.194
You've got a minute
before we get company.

03:14.803 --> 03:17.806
Emma! Emma!

03:17.806 --> 03:21.636
Hey! Ask that pervert
what he did with my daughter!

03:21.636 --> 03:23.203
Yeah, I'd love to,
but you shot him,

03:23.203 --> 03:24.508
so he's not taking questions
right now. Can you shut up?

03:24.508 --> 03:26.641
Kick him in the nuts!
See if he wakes up.

03:26.641 --> 03:30.166
Would you shut up, Paul?!
Is she here, you think?

03:30.166 --> 03:32.168
No. Curtains are open.
Neighbors are close.

03:32.168 --> 03:34.214
No basement.

03:53.711 --> 03:57.062
He got up with
a gunshot wound to the abdomen

03:57.062 --> 03:59.674
to lock the door then
came back here and passed out.

03:59.674 --> 04:00.979
Why?

04:00.979 --> 04:03.199
So Will Trent
can't get in his house.

04:06.202 --> 04:10.424
There's something in there
he didn't want us to see.

04:12.469 --> 04:15.124
How much detail
am I supposed to put in this?

04:15.124 --> 04:17.300
As much detail
as you can possibly remember,

04:17.300 --> 04:19.215
starting from the moment
you thought it was a good idea

04:19.215 --> 04:20.477
to take a gun to his house.

04:22.000 --> 04:23.219
What are you doing
to find my daughter?

04:23.219 --> 04:24.438
Will is at the hospital.

04:24.438 --> 04:27.223
He'll talk to Evan
as soon as he wakes up.

04:27.223 --> 04:28.572
How are you feeling?
Are you still drunk?

04:28.572 --> 04:31.227
I wish.

04:31.227 --> 04:33.229
You keep in touch with anyone?
Mrs. Flanagan?

04:33.229 --> 04:36.232
Uh, she passed away
10 years ago already.

04:36.232 --> 04:37.755
May she rest in peace.

04:38.669 --> 04:40.628
I still keep my hankie. You?

04:40.628 --> 04:41.629
Sure, I'm a lady.

04:43.152 --> 04:44.284
You and Will, though.

04:45.763 --> 04:47.156
Me and Will.

04:47.156 --> 04:50.246
You guys always had each other.
Must've been nice.

04:50.246 --> 04:51.639
Well, I guess you still do.

04:51.639 --> 04:53.989
Honestly, I don't know
if that's romantic or sad.

04:55.164 --> 04:57.035
Yeah, it's a little of both.

04:57.035 --> 04:58.733
You think about that time much,
when we were kids?

04:58.733 --> 05:00.256
You do any therapy?

05:00.256 --> 05:02.954
Oh, thinking about the past
always gets me in trouble.

05:02.954 --> 05:05.261
In general, I like
to keep it moving forward.

05:05.261 --> 05:06.262
Hundred percent.

05:07.481 --> 05:09.613
You and I were
never so different.

05:09.613 --> 05:11.311
Yeah, except you seem
like kind of a douche

05:11.311 --> 05:13.443
and, uh, you're going to jail.

05:13.443 --> 05:15.271
True.

05:15.271 --> 05:18.100
I also drive a much better car
than you because I'm rich,

05:18.100 --> 05:19.884
which means I'll be out
in two hours.

05:19.884 --> 05:21.277
Yeah, well, you got me there.

05:21.277 --> 05:22.800
- Mm-hmm.
- Wait.

05:22.800 --> 05:25.281
Evan was on the phone
when he opened the door?

05:25.281 --> 05:26.500
Mm-hmm.

05:32.288 --> 05:33.898
Ahh.

05:33.898 --> 05:36.510
