05:36.510 --> 05:38.381
What is everyone staring at?

05:38.381 --> 05:40.035
Oh, well,
everyone's very interested

05:40.035 --> 05:42.254
in the fact that you were at
Will Trent's house at 4:00 a.m.

05:42.254 --> 05:44.735
when Paul Campano showed up with
a bloody shirt, including me.

05:44.735 --> 05:46.302
I'm your sponsor.
I got a lot of questions.

05:46.302 --> 05:47.303
Oh.

05:49.566 --> 05:52.308
Everybody knows?
Does Heller know?

05:52.308 --> 05:54.528
Oh, honey.
Even the cleaning lady knows.

05:55.964 --> 05:57.313
How long has this
been going on for?

05:57.313 --> 05:58.793
25 years.

05:58.793 --> 05:59.794
Excuse me?

06:03.580 --> 06:06.017
You know how I said
I grew up in a group home?

06:06.017 --> 06:08.846
Well, Will was there.

06:08.846 --> 06:11.632
So he and I are--
He's like my arm,

06:11.632 --> 06:12.763
if I was in a lifelong,

06:12.763 --> 06:14.939
on-and-off relationship
with my arm.

06:14.939 --> 06:17.594
Mm-hmm. We call that
co-dependent in the program.

06:17.594 --> 06:19.335
Is being in a relationship
with someone

06:19.335 --> 06:21.424
that reminds you of
the worst time in your life

06:21.424 --> 06:22.991
- good for your sobriety?
- No, no, no, no!

06:22.991 --> 06:24.471
It's fine,
because what we do is,

06:24.471 --> 06:25.863
we don't talk about
anything that matters.

06:25.863 --> 06:27.343
Oh.

06:27.343 --> 06:29.214
Um, okay, so,
speaking of sobriety,

06:29.214 --> 06:30.781
yesterday,
when I was undercover,

06:30.781 --> 06:33.001
I had to wear a fentanyl patch
for a half-hour.

06:33.001 --> 06:35.046
But it-- I took it off.
It's fine. No big deal.

06:35.046 --> 06:36.352
Sounds like
a very big deal to me.

06:36.352 --> 06:39.224
Look. Get a meeting today, okay?

06:39.224 --> 06:40.400
Yes, yes, totally.

06:40.400 --> 06:42.358
Hey! I got something for you.

06:42.358 --> 06:43.707
What you got?

06:43.707 --> 06:45.622
So, Paul said that
when Evan answered the door,

06:45.622 --> 06:47.972
he was on a phone,
a "cheap" black phone.

06:47.972 --> 06:50.366
A burner.

06:53.413 --> 06:55.676
That's why he went back in.

07:00.332 --> 07:02.378
- So, did you talk to him?
<i>- Not awake.</i>

07:02.378 --> 07:05.990
I'll get him to tell me
who he is, if he ever wakes up.

07:05.990 --> 07:08.384
Hey, um...

07:08.384 --> 07:09.820
glad you came by last night.

07:09.820 --> 07:11.648
<i>It was fun.</i>

07:11.648 --> 07:13.084
Before Paul crashed the party.

07:13.084 --> 07:14.608
Uh, yeah.

07:14.608 --> 07:17.393
Everyone at APD knows
I was at your house last night,

07:17.393 --> 07:19.787
so that is awesome for me.

07:19.787 --> 07:21.441
Well, my stock just went way up.

07:21.441 --> 07:23.094
Yeah, well,
mine just went way down.

07:23.094 --> 07:25.401
Why?
Everyone at APD loves me.

07:27.447 --> 07:30.406
Screw it.
Cat's out the bag.

07:30.406 --> 07:33.104
Let's go out to dinner.
Like a date.

07:33.104 --> 07:34.758
We don't date.

07:34.758 --> 07:37.544
We scurry around in the shadows
and wallow in shame.

07:37.544 --> 07:38.893
I'm just saying,
let's try something new.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.636
<i>Come on. Let's go to dinner.</i>

07:42.636 --> 07:44.594
We can still wallow
in shame after.

07:44.594 --> 07:47.902
All right. You're on.

07:47.902 --> 07:50.382
Find the girl so you can
take me out for a steak.

07:52.036 --> 07:53.168
On it.

07:53.168 --> 07:54.430
- All right.
- Let's go, partner.

07:54.430 --> 07:56.519
We caught a body in Grove Park.

07:56.519 --> 07:58.434
Hey, does Trent keep the vest on
during sex?

08:00.697 --> 08:01.872
Yeah.

08:07.051 --> 08:08.662
What the hell
are you doing here?

08:08.662 --> 08:10.533
Will's at the hospital waiting
to interview Evan Bernard.

08:10.533 --> 08:12.361
Who?

08:12.361 --> 08:14.755
Paul Campano shot one of
Emma's teacher's last night.

08:14.755 --> 08:17.453
He thinks he had
his daughter kidnapped.

08:17.453 --> 08:19.499
I should not have to
recap your case to you.

08:19.499 --> 08:21.457
- Well, I didn't know.
- Well, why didn't you know?

08:21.457 --> 08:24.460
Am I gonna regret
putting you on this case?

08:24.460 --> 08:26.027
No, ma'am.

08:30.074 --> 08:32.642
Agent Trent? He's awake.

08:32.642 --> 08:34.339
Did you find a cellphone on him
when he arrived?

08:34.339 --> 08:37.125
Not that I know of.

08:37.125 --> 08:38.822
I'm gonna send someone
to look through the trash.

08:38.822 --> 08:39.997
Will you make sure
it doesn't get collected?

08:42.565 --> 08:45.263
<i>Dr. Caplan, extension 2366.</i>

08:45.263 --> 08:46.787
Evan Bernard?

08:46.787 --> 08:49.572
Special Agent Will Trent,
Georgia Bureau of Investigation.

08:49.572 --> 08:50.878
You want to tell me
what happened?

08:50.878 --> 08:53.489
Sure. Uh, Paul Campano
came to my house.

08:53.489 --> 08:55.491
He was drunk and enraged

08:55.491 --> 08:57.493
and accused me
of kidnapping his daughter.

08:57.493 --> 08:59.626
I asked him to leave,
and he proceeded to shoot me.

08:59.626 --> 09:02.411
Mr. Campano says you were
on the phone when he arrived.

09:02.411 --> 09:05.545
No. Uh, he woke me
from a dead sleep.

09:05.545 --> 09:07.677
Did you happen to go back
into the house after he left?

09:07.677 --> 09:10.506
After he shot me?
No. I was unconscious.

09:10.506 --> 09:14.510
I saw you started your career
at the university level.

09:14.510 --> 09:15.946
Why the switch to high school?

09:17.469 --> 09:19.559
I like to be the one
to open young minds.

09:20.864 --> 09:22.953
Hmm. You do some tutoring, too.

09:22.953 --> 09:24.520
Gotta make ends meet.

09:24.520 --> 09:25.521
You having financial problems?

09:25.521 --> 09:26.740
Oh, who doesn't?

09:26.740 --> 09:28.568
Well, the Campanos
are doing pretty well.

09:30.047 --> 09:31.527
Do you ever tutor any students

09:31.527 --> 09:33.616
with learning disabilities, dyslexia?

09:33.616 --> 09:35.618
Yes, I-I tutor some students
with dyslexia.

09:35.618 --> 09:37.968
You ever tutor a young man
by the name of Warren Grier?

09:38.839 --> 09:40.101
Never heard of him.

09:40.101 --> 09:41.929
You sure? Take a second.

09:41.929 --> 09:44.192
Slight build? Curly blond hair?

09:44.192 --> 09:45.802
Committed suicide last night?

09:46.716 --> 09:49.371
I'm positive.

09:49.371 --> 09:50.590
Are we through here?

09:50.590 --> 09:52.069
Not quite.
Did you know Kayla Alexander?

09:53.505 --> 09:54.637
I don't know her personally,

09:54.637 --> 09:56.552
but I understand
she's quite a handful.

09:56.552 --> 09:58.728
Not anymore, right? She's dead.

10:01.601 --> 10:03.211
What about Emma?
You were her teacher, right?

10:03.211 --> 10:04.952
Then she transferred
out of your class. Why?

10:04.952 --> 10:07.041
She took
a less-challenging course.

10:07.041 --> 10:08.564
Not everyone's ready
for "Beowulf."

10:08.564 --> 10:10.218
Did you ever make
a sexual advance on her?

10:13.613 --> 10:14.831
Okay.

10:16.354 --> 10:18.443
I gotta piss like a racehorse.
Help me to the bathroom?

10:18.443 --> 10:20.097
- Let me get some help.
- Uh, just...

10:21.577 --> 10:23.579
Why don't you just
get the door for me?

10:23.579 --> 10:24.624
All right.

10:28.671 --> 10:29.890
Sign says "pull."

10:29.890 --> 10:32.457
Yeah. I got it.

10:32.457 --> 10:34.416
I noticed you don't take notes,
Agent Trent.

10:34.416 --> 10:36.461
I have a good memory.

10:36.461 --> 10:38.594
Plus, I'm a pretty
observant guy.

10:43.077 --> 10:46.646
I have never done anything
inappropriate with a student.

10:46.646 --> 10:47.864
Ever.

10:49.649 --> 10:52.260
Any chance we could take a look
around your place?

10:56.656 --> 10:58.353
I want to talk to my lawyer.

11:00.311 --> 11:02.792
Oh, by all means.

11:02.792 --> 11:04.838
I'll be in touch.

11:07.362 --> 11:10.452
Evan Bernard presents
as arrogant and intelligent.

11:10.452 --> 11:12.149
He stated a preference
for softer targets

11:12.149 --> 11:14.108
by switching from university
to high-school teaching--

11:14.108 --> 11:15.718
I need you to keep me
in the loop.

11:15.718 --> 11:17.633
He wanted to end the interview
when Warren's name came up,

11:17.633 --> 11:20.636
and he denigrated both Kayla
Alexander and Emma Campano.

11:20.636 --> 11:22.246
The bathroom thing
was a power move.

11:22.246 --> 11:23.465
He also doesn't miss a thing.

11:23.465 --> 11:24.553
He's our guy. It's him.

11:24.553 --> 11:26.207
Oh, I'm sorry.
I need to take this.

11:28.078 --> 11:30.472
When?

11:30.472 --> 11:31.821
Okay. We'll be right there.

11:31.821 --> 11:33.562
I don't see
how it could be your guy.

11:33.562 --> 11:35.433
Abigail Campano
just got a ransom call

11:35.433 --> 11:36.478
five minutes ago.

11:36.478 --> 11:37.653
They want $3 million.

11:44.704 --> 11:47.402
Mommy, please.

11:47.402 --> 11:49.752
<i>Just pay them
whatever they want.</i>

11:51.536 --> 11:53.887
<i>I just want to come home.</i>

11:53.887 --> 11:55.540
<i>I'm so scared.</i>

11:57.151 --> 11:58.587
Stop the video.

11:58.587 --> 12:01.982
Mrs. Campano, I need you
to focus on the background.

12:01.982 --> 12:03.418
Do you recognize anything?

12:03.418 --> 12:05.681
The wood paneling,
the-- the blanket, the pillow?

12:05.681 --> 12:06.682
Does anything look familiar?

12:06.682 --> 12:08.684
I don't recognize any of it.

12:08.684 --> 12:10.599
My father has the money in cash.

12:10.599 --> 12:12.383
That's a bad idea.

12:12.383 --> 12:13.515
We strongly recommend against

12:13.515 --> 12:14.690
paying the ransom
in every case.

12:14.690 --> 12:16.561
No! That's how we get Emma back!

12:16.561 --> 12:17.954
If they get the money,

12:17.954 --> 12:19.260
there's nothing stopping them
from killing her.

12:19.260 --> 12:21.566
Do you have a better idea?

12:22.567 --> 12:24.395
Evan Bernard knows
more than he's saying.

12:24.395 --> 12:27.398
Oh, you mean the reputable
teacher that my husband shot?

12:27.398 --> 12:30.097
I think he was in the hospital
when the call came in.

12:30.097 --> 12:31.707
He must be working
with an accomplice.

12:31.707 --> 12:32.752
Do you have evidence of that?

12:35.798 --> 12:38.105
Not yet. Just give me six hours.

12:38.105 --> 12:39.933
Let me go to the school
and talk to some people.

12:39.933 --> 12:42.849
We can stall the ransom
until then.

12:42.849 --> 12:44.764
Mrs. Campano.

12:46.853 --> 12:47.767
Please.

12:52.641 --> 12:53.773
I'll give you six hours.

12:56.819 --> 12:57.951
You better be right about this.

13:02.912 --> 13:05.785
The hospital found this
in a pillow case. No prints.

13:07.961 --> 13:10.311
You're going to the school
without me, aren't you?

13:10.311 --> 13:11.878
Yes.

13:11.878 --> 13:14.794
You're welcome to come.

13:14.794 --> 13:16.752
I'm "welcome to come"?

13:16.752 --> 13:18.754
How wonderful.

13:18.754 --> 13:19.799
Actually, you can drive.

13:27.241 --> 13:30.766
Why Will Trent, of all people?

13:30.766 --> 13:32.768
What floor is our body on?

13:32.768 --> 13:34.248
Eighth.

13:34.248 --> 13:36.685
Come on. Tell me.

13:36.685 --> 13:38.513
His clearance rate
puts yours to shame.

13:38.513 --> 13:40.863
Is that a euphemism?

13:40.863 --> 13:42.996
Yeah. Maybe it is.
We gotta stop.

13:42.996 --> 13:44.693
I'm having a cardiac event.

13:44.693 --> 13:46.216
Well, it's not like
she can get more dead.

13:48.218 --> 13:49.785
He's good police.

13:49.785 --> 13:51.743
Okay?
Competence, that's sexy.

13:51.743 --> 13:53.441
And he's objectively hot.

13:53.441 --> 13:56.531
And you know what else?
He listens, Ormewood.

13:56.531 --> 13:57.793
Underrated quality in a man.

13:59.926 --> 14:01.884
I'm sorry.
Did you say something?

14:01.884 --> 14:04.800
My mind just kind of
wandered off there.

14:04.800 --> 14:06.236
I guess I'm just a simple man.

14:06.236 --> 14:07.629
Funny.

14:07.629 --> 14:09.805
I'm kidding.

14:09.805 --> 14:12.199
Okay.

14:12.199 --> 14:13.853
Only five more flights.

14:16.681 --> 14:17.813
Body's in there.

14:17.813 --> 14:19.859
- Landlord's waiting inside.
- Okay.

14:19.859 --> 14:21.904
Okay.

14:24.385 --> 14:26.866
There she is.

14:26.866 --> 14:29.520
She had a lot of visitors,
if you get my drift.

14:31.261 --> 14:33.089
Uh, blunt-force trauma
to the head.

14:33.089 --> 14:35.222
How long has that elevator
been out?

14:35.222 --> 14:37.398
You investigating the building
or the murder?

14:37.398 --> 14:39.835
The murder, for now.
Watch the tone.

14:39.835 --> 14:41.445
Were you the one who found her?

14:41.445 --> 14:43.752
Yeah.
She was late for her rent,

14:43.752 --> 14:46.102
so I came up,
the door was wide open.

14:46.102 --> 14:47.843
Uh-huh.

14:49.671 --> 14:51.847
Hey, Polaski, come here!

14:51.847 --> 14:53.457
Yeah. What you got?

14:59.855 --> 15:02.771
Ooh. What could this mean?

15:02.771 --> 15:05.861
I mean, I'm no Will Trent, but
let me read this crime scene.

15:05.861 --> 15:07.645
Thinking maybe somebody else
might've been here

15:07.645 --> 15:10.866
at the time of the murder,
dyeing their hair... blue?

15:13.913 --> 15:15.827
Let's see where this trail
takes us.

15:26.403 --> 15:28.188
Should we knock?

15:28.188 --> 15:30.755
What would Will Trent do?

15:30.755 --> 15:31.887
You want to give him a call
and ask?

15:31.887 --> 15:32.975
All right.
I'm tired of this bit.

15:32.975 --> 15:34.672
APD! Open up!

15:36.196 --> 15:37.545
Open this door,
or I'll kick it in!

15:37.545 --> 15:39.939
Will you calm down?
You can't act like this anymore.

15:41.941 --> 15:44.421
I didn't kill her, I swear.
I know this looks bad.

15:45.945 --> 15:48.382
Hey, wait up!

15:48.382 --> 15:49.557
We need to talk.

15:51.298 --> 15:52.908
Hey. Listen.

15:52.908 --> 15:55.563
Do you think a dog can
get their feelings hurt?

15:55.563 --> 15:56.912
I haven't given it much thought,

15:56.912 --> 15:59.001
but I suppose it's a good idea

15:59.001 --> 16:02.874
to treat all of God's creatures
with kindness and respect.

16:02.874 --> 16:04.920
To that end, the next time
that you get a lead on our case

16:04.920 --> 16:07.096
in the middle of the night,
call me.

16:07.096 --> 16:09.142
I don't care if Angie Polaski
is in your bed.

16:09.142 --> 16:12.928
Wow.
Everyone knows, huh? Amanda?

16:12.928 --> 16:14.974
Amanda probably knew
before it happened.

16:14.974 --> 16:16.540
I heard what you were saying
about Evan

16:16.540 --> 16:18.107
in your little
tape-recorder diary thing.

16:18.107 --> 16:20.588
- Those are my notes.
- Whatever. Talk me through it.

16:20.588 --> 16:21.893
Warren Grier
was working with someone

16:21.893 --> 16:23.156
who had a hold on him,

16:23.156 --> 16:24.940
someone with so much
influence and control

16:24.940 --> 16:27.421
that he convinced Warren
to kill himself.

16:27.421 --> 16:29.510
Evan Bernard fits that profile
to a "T."

16:29.510 --> 16:30.946
He gets off on power.

16:30.946 --> 16:32.948
Yeah, but what about the ransom?

16:32.948 --> 16:34.602
You think this is
financially motivated?

16:34.602 --> 16:36.996
Sure. Money is power.

16:36.996 --> 16:38.954
Paul swears
he made a move on Emma.

16:38.954 --> 16:40.782
She rejected him
by switching teachers,

16:40.782 --> 16:42.436
so punishment for rejecting him

16:42.436 --> 16:43.698
with the bonus
of financial gain.

16:44.829 --> 16:46.353
Works for me.

16:46.353 --> 16:48.833
We just need
a second accomplice.

16:48.833 --> 16:51.184
Yeah.
Feels like a student.

16:51.184 --> 16:52.881
Agree.

16:52.881 --> 16:54.970
You see how easy that was?

16:54.970 --> 16:56.667
Keep your partner looped in.
It's fun.

17:01.890 --> 17:03.196
Consider yourself
especially "looped in"

17:03.196 --> 17:04.284
for this next part.

17:06.634 --> 17:09.245
I'm just gonna miss her so much!

17:10.594 --> 17:12.031
You were close with Kayla?

17:12.031 --> 17:13.989
Oh, God, no.
No, Kayla was awful.

17:13.989 --> 17:15.991
Emma was so sweet, though.

17:15.991 --> 17:17.079
We want to ask you
about Evan Bernard.

17:17.079 --> 17:18.298
Did he do something?

17:20.169 --> 17:22.215
He just wrote me a letter
of recommendation to Stanford.

17:22.215 --> 17:23.477
Is this going to affect that?

17:23.477 --> 17:25.783
Feels like we're focusing
on the wrong thing.

17:25.783 --> 17:27.916
I heard he was shot last night.

17:27.916 --> 17:30.745
Oh, my God! What is happening?!

17:30.745 --> 17:33.226
Is this a serial killer?
Is he hunting a certain type?

17:33.226 --> 17:36.011
Just want to steer
the conversation back to Evan--

17:36.011 --> 17:37.360
Emma and Kayla both had
long, blond hair.

17:37.360 --> 17:38.492
Do I need to cut my hair?

17:38.492 --> 17:39.754
- We have no reason to think--
- Yes.

17:39.754 --> 17:42.844
Can we get back to Mr. Bernard?

17:42.844 --> 17:44.019
Which of the students
were close to him?

17:46.978 --> 17:49.068
Well... there are
the Kayla rumors.

17:50.504 --> 17:51.635
What Kayla rumors?

17:58.686 --> 18:01.906
Kayla and Evan
sleeping together! Oh, my God.

18:01.906 --> 18:03.865
What is going on here?

18:03.865 --> 18:05.954
Special Agent Will Trent, GBI.

18:05.954 --> 18:08.130
We're looking into
the kidnapping of Emma Campano.

18:08.130 --> 18:10.698
I would appreciate it
if you went through my office.

18:10.698 --> 18:12.091
Girls, get to class.

18:13.092 --> 18:15.442
You two, come with me.

18:16.269 --> 18:18.706
You said Kayla had consensual
sex yesterday morning.

18:18.706 --> 18:19.750
- Gotta be Evan.
- Mm-hmm.

18:19.750 --> 18:22.231
Get the DNA back
on Paul's shirt.

18:22.231 --> 18:23.102
On it.

18:24.494 --> 18:27.628
You guys want water
or anything?

18:27.628 --> 18:31.197
I have tap or cold tap.

18:31.197 --> 18:33.982
No. Nico, we want you
to tell us what happened.

18:33.982 --> 18:35.723
All right,
let's take Nico here

18:35.723 --> 18:37.333
down to the police station.

18:37.333 --> 18:38.639
She's either the witness
or the do-er.

18:38.639 --> 18:39.727
They/them!

18:39.727 --> 18:41.946
Okay, I wanted to dye my hair

18:41.946 --> 18:44.949
because it looked like ass,
but my shower is broken.

18:44.949 --> 18:47.691
Almost everybody's shower
is broken.

18:47.691 --> 18:49.171
Sasha said I could use hers.

18:49.171 --> 18:52.174
And when I got out
of the shower,

18:52.174 --> 18:56.439
all I heard was screaming
and yelling and then fighting

18:56.439 --> 18:59.225
and then a terrible sound...

18:59.225 --> 19:00.965
and then nothing.

19:03.142 --> 19:05.100
Sasha was dead.

19:05.100 --> 19:07.102
And I thought...

19:07.102 --> 19:09.104
That it looked bad for you.

19:09.104 --> 19:10.932
It does look bad for you.

19:10.932 --> 19:13.500
Found a blue handprint
on the window.

19:13.500 --> 19:14.936
Seems like you might
have seen something.

19:17.156 --> 19:20.115
No. Okay, well, did you
recognize the voice?

19:20.115 --> 19:21.812
- No!
- "No"?

19:21.812 --> 19:24.337
Well, that's a lie. And I've had
about enough of you.

19:24.337 --> 19:25.381
So let's go!

19:25.381 --> 19:28.123
Yo, calm down!

19:28.123 --> 19:31.039
Can I get some ranch dressing
and some extra napkins, please?

19:31.039 --> 19:32.301
- Sure.
- This is me.

19:33.346 --> 19:35.130
Hey, how old
do you think Nico is?

19:35.130 --> 19:36.914
Not a day over 16.

19:36.914 --> 19:38.133
Maybe we should
call her parents.

19:38.133 --> 19:40.570
No! Don't call my parents!
Please.

19:40.570 --> 19:41.789
Don't make me go back there.

19:43.965 --> 19:45.184
- Excuse me.
- There you go.

19:47.577 --> 19:49.536
Hey, you left the door open!

19:49.536 --> 19:51.364
She's eating your fries!

19:51.364 --> 19:53.148
They/them. It's not that hard.

19:53.148 --> 19:54.845
Well, you can cancel me
from jail.

19:54.845 --> 19:56.064
Hey, you.

19:56.064 --> 19:59.154
Hey, um, any chance you could

19:59.154 --> 20:00.721
drop by my house
and check on Betty?

20:00.721 --> 20:02.592
When did we get married?

20:02.592 --> 20:04.681
I feel terrible I yelled at her.

20:07.641 --> 20:09.077
Yeah, I could do that.

20:09.077 --> 20:10.644
Thank you.
Um, can you also just

20:10.644 --> 20:12.254
put a little bit of water
in her food?

20:12.254 --> 20:14.169
I think her teeth
are bothering her.

20:14.169 --> 20:16.171
<i>And, you know, maybe put
a little bit of music on.</i>

20:16.171 --> 20:19.218
Um, something upbeat, like
OutKast. That'd be fun, right?

20:19.218 --> 20:21.132
No, no, that might
overstimulate her.

20:21.132 --> 20:22.873
Let's--
Maybe more like Sam Cooke?

20:22.873 --> 20:25.615
Oh, my God. Who are you?
Just-- I gotta go.

20:25.615 --> 20:27.878
Okay. Thank you. Bye. Hi.

20:27.878 --> 20:30.185
Hi. I'm Mary Clark,
the guidance counselor.

20:30.185 --> 20:32.231
I can take you two
to Evan Bernard's office.

20:32.231 --> 20:35.625
Okay, great. How long has
Evan Bernard worked here?

20:35.625 --> 20:37.366
Uh, four or five years.

20:37.366 --> 20:39.629
There's a rumor that he
and Kayla were having sex.

20:41.240 --> 20:43.590
I never heard or saw
anything like that.

20:43.590 --> 20:45.418
We take that
very seriously here.

20:45.418 --> 20:47.420
We'll have to open
an investigation.

20:48.812 --> 20:52.120
I know all the girls here
pretty well.

20:52.120 --> 20:55.210
If you have any questions,
please reach out.

20:55.210 --> 20:58.213
We all want nothing more
than to find Emma.

21:00.868 --> 21:02.261
The DNA from the shirt

21:02.261 --> 21:04.001
won't be back
for another 48 hours.

21:04.001 --> 21:06.047
No, we have three hours
until Abigail pays the ransom.

21:06.047 --> 21:07.875
I need it now! Call the lab.

21:08.963 --> 21:11.313
Okay. I'll just go...

21:11.313 --> 21:13.272
yell at science.

21:17.058 --> 21:20.235
The area is clean and orderly.

21:25.240 --> 21:26.850
Who were you talking to

21:26.850 --> 21:28.896
when Paul knocked on the door,
Evan, huh?

21:31.202 --> 21:33.901
Grooming supplies
in the top drawer.

21:33.901 --> 21:35.598
Everything in here says creep.

21:38.122 --> 21:39.210
Can I help you find something?

21:39.210 --> 21:41.387
I'm finding everything I need.

21:41.387 --> 21:43.127
Nice tape recorder.

21:43.127 --> 21:44.477
Is that how you take notes?

21:44.477 --> 21:46.261
Mind if I record
this conversation?

21:46.261 --> 21:47.697
Sure.

21:47.697 --> 21:49.656
A lot of my students
use recording devices to cope.

21:51.135 --> 21:52.267
You know what?
I'm glad you're here, Evan.

21:52.267 --> 21:54.138
Saves me a trip.

21:54.138 --> 21:56.271
We pulled your DNA off
of Paul Campano's shirt,

21:56.271 --> 21:58.273
and it's an exact match

21:58.273 --> 21:59.840
for the semen found
on Kayla Alexander.

22:02.016 --> 22:05.062
We are in Georgia.
Age of consent is 17.

22:06.107 --> 22:08.283
You're not gonna even bother to
at least look a little ashamed?

22:08.283 --> 22:09.937
She was of age
and she wasn't coerced,

22:09.937 --> 22:10.938
so I haven't broken any laws.

22:12.505 --> 22:14.289
Well, except you have.

22:14.289 --> 22:17.248
You're a member of the faculty
at this school.

22:17.248 --> 22:19.294
That makes you her guardian.

22:19.294 --> 22:20.339
In loco parentis.

22:22.732 --> 22:24.299
You're under arrest.

22:25.300 --> 22:27.955
I'll be out on bail in 24 hours.

22:27.955 --> 22:29.522
Yeah, maybe by that time,
we'll find some other stuff

22:29.522 --> 22:32.220
to charge you with after we take
a look around your house.

22:32.220 --> 22:33.526
The lab says that
the DNA from the shirt's

22:33.526 --> 22:36.355
not coming back
until tomorrow morning...

22:36.355 --> 22:37.399
earliest.

22:39.619 --> 22:40.794
Played a hunch.

22:45.364 --> 22:47.714
He's working with an
accomplice. They could be armed.

22:47.714 --> 22:50.238
Go, go, go!

22:51.805 --> 22:53.589
Clear!

22:53.589 --> 22:56.505
- AGENT â™ª1: Clear!
- AGENT â™ª2: Clear!

22:56.505 --> 22:57.680
All clear!

23:01.989 --> 23:05.122
Whew! Bleach.

23:05.122 --> 23:06.385
You could do surgery in here.

23:07.473 --> 23:09.866
Guys? You gotta see this.

23:19.963 --> 23:23.358
Okay, but why clean the whole
house and keep this here?

23:23.358 --> 23:24.403
He's showing off.

23:24.403 --> 23:25.882
Yeah, but why?

23:25.882 --> 23:28.319
He's having fun with us.
Son of a bitch.

23:33.934 --> 23:35.892
- Yeah.
- Hey!

23:35.892 --> 23:38.199
Look at you!

23:38.199 --> 23:39.766
Weird little purse dog, huh?

23:39.766 --> 23:42.246
Hello! Hi!

23:42.246 --> 23:44.771
She's so cute!

23:44.771 --> 23:47.382
Whose house is this? It's nice.

23:47.382 --> 23:49.079
It's my friend Will's house.

23:49.079 --> 23:52.039
You know, when he was your age,
he had a rough go of things...

23:52.039 --> 23:54.389
but turned it around,

23:54.389 --> 23:56.217
made a nice life for himself.

23:56.217 --> 23:58.045
Anything's possible, huh?

23:59.438 --> 24:02.528
Nico, in my line of work,
you tell yourself stories

24:02.528 --> 24:04.443
when you're trying
to figure things out.

24:04.443 --> 24:06.227
And since
you haven't been talking,

24:06.227 --> 24:07.620
I've been making one up.

24:07.620 --> 24:11.493
It has to do with that
awful landlord of yours...

24:11.493 --> 24:15.323
and Sasha having
the only working shower.

24:15.323 --> 24:18.413
I'm thinking...
maybe she was trading sex

24:18.413 --> 24:20.110
for favors from him.

24:21.285 --> 24:23.374
No judgment.
Everybody's gotta survive.

24:23.374 --> 24:25.681
But maybe she wanted to stop.

24:28.075 --> 24:29.424
And guys like that can be scary

24:29.424 --> 24:31.339
when they don't get
what they want.

24:33.254 --> 24:35.952
She was my friend.

24:42.829 --> 24:46.136
Then let's do
this one last thing for her.

24:50.837 --> 24:52.099
It was the landlord.

24:53.317 --> 24:54.362
I saw him in the alley.

24:54.362 --> 24:56.059
He threw something
in the dumpster.

24:57.496 --> 24:59.019
He threw something
in the dumpster?

24:59.019 --> 25:00.455
Yeah.

25:00.455 --> 25:02.283
It-- It looked like a hammer.

25:03.980 --> 25:05.373
Great.

25:05.373 --> 25:09.682
That's really good. Okay.

25:09.682 --> 25:11.553
Let's go get this guy, Nico.

25:13.207 --> 25:15.775
Yes, sir, that is correct.
Demetrius is on the way up.

25:15.775 --> 25:18.473
Well, I gotta get the number
of your cleaning lady.

25:18.473 --> 25:19.518
Your place is immaculate.

25:21.345 --> 25:23.173
Especially that pedophile suite.

25:23.173 --> 25:24.392
Is that where you brought Emma?

25:26.525 --> 25:29.092
<i>What, you think you're special?</i>

25:29.092 --> 25:32.879
<i>You're just a garden-variety
abuser with a good education.</i>

25:32.879 --> 25:35.577
Do Paul and Abigail Campano know
that the lead investigator

25:35.577 --> 25:38.145
on their daughter's
active kidnapping case

25:38.145 --> 25:39.886
is functionally illiterate?

25:42.105 --> 25:44.543
I'm a pretty observant guy, too.

25:46.545 --> 25:47.763
You used the word "shame"
earlier.

25:47.763 --> 25:49.417
Is that a big theme
in your life?

25:49.417 --> 25:50.636
How old were you, huh,

25:50.636 --> 25:52.594
when you realized
you weren't... keeping up?

25:52.594 --> 25:54.596
- Where is Emma, Evan?
- Is your whole life

25:54.596 --> 25:56.424
organized around
keeping your secret?

25:56.424 --> 25:57.947
- Where is she?
- You really think

25:57.947 --> 26:00.776
that that costume you wear
keeps people from seeing you?

26:00.776 --> 26:03.518
I figured it out in two moves.

26:03.518 --> 26:05.172
Not everybody
is as perceptive as me,

26:05.172 --> 26:07.087
but I bet most people
get a whiff

26:07.087 --> 26:09.568
that something is just... off.

26:11.787 --> 26:14.660
I'm gonna find Emma.

26:14.660 --> 26:16.444
And I'm gonna put you away.

26:16.444 --> 26:17.532
Know that.

26:28.978 --> 26:29.979
Who saw that?

26:29.979 --> 26:31.415
What the hell happened in there?

26:31.415 --> 26:33.417
I got made, is what happened!
Who else saw that?!

26:33.417 --> 26:35.942
Just me. So that's it?

26:35.942 --> 26:37.204
You let this guy
get under your skin,

26:37.204 --> 26:39.467
and we just sit there,
chicken in hand?

26:39.467 --> 26:41.556
Your six hours is up.
Abigail wants to pay.

26:41.556 --> 26:43.819
- That's a terrible idea!
- I know!

26:43.819 --> 26:45.168
So what's your next play?

26:46.779 --> 26:48.955
You've operated this way
your entire career,

26:48.955 --> 26:50.478
and you're the best I have.

26:50.478 --> 26:51.827
Maybe it's time
to get over yourself

26:51.827 --> 26:52.741
and ask for some help.

26:55.788 --> 26:57.267
No?

27:00.575 --> 27:02.142
Caroline, get Faith in here.

27:02.142 --> 27:03.491
<i>Yes, ma'am.</i>

27:03.491 --> 27:05.580
Use Faith. She's smart.

27:05.580 --> 27:06.842
And she can read.

27:07.713 --> 27:10.672
Oh, that's low, even for you.

27:10.672 --> 27:12.631
What's up?

27:18.419 --> 27:20.421
Go through everything we found
at the recording studio.

27:20.421 --> 27:21.683
We must have missed something.

27:21.683 --> 27:23.337
See if you can find
anything that connects

27:23.337 --> 27:24.599
Warren Grier to Evan Bernard.

27:24.599 --> 27:26.427
Yeah, the uniforms
are already doing that.

27:26.427 --> 27:28.037
I don't know those uniforms!

27:28.037 --> 27:30.474
I know you,
and I'm asking you to do it!

27:30.474 --> 27:31.650
Well, where are you going?

27:33.826 --> 27:35.654
To tell the Campanos
to pay the ransom.

27:43.662 --> 27:46.229
If I get Hep "C" from a needle,
I'm suing the department.

27:46.229 --> 27:47.709
You probably already have
Hep "C."

27:50.669 --> 27:52.627
Hey, listen, I wanted
to tell you that I--

27:52.627 --> 27:54.498
I'm just gonna
